      <div class="wrap pl-4 pr-4">
        <h2>Flourish</h2>
        <p class="f6">
          The Flourish component works hand in hand with a set of syles, using
          the <code>.dropcap</code> class. This will uses CSS to dropcap the first
          letter in the first <code>p</code> tag it encounters.
        </p>
        <h3>Flourish Classes</h3>
        <p class="f6 bt">
          <code>.dropcap</code> also has a set of CSS custom properties that are
          a subset of our brand colors. These are prefixed
          <code>--dc-color-name</code>, and can be used to add color to your
          drop cap charecter.
        </p>
        <section>
          <h3>Flourish Use</h3>
          <div class="bt">
            <pre><code>&lt;Flourish classes=&#x7b;['--rowan-leaves', 'dropcap', '--dc-brand-purple-dk']&#x7b;&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Some text...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/Flourish&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
          <h3>Flourish Properties</h3>
          <div class="grid pa-0 grid-cols-3 pb-4 bt">
            <ul class="list f7">
              <li><code>--alder</code></li>
              <li><code>--apple</code></li>
              <li><code>--aspen</code></li>
              <li><code>--beech</code></li>
              <li><code>--downybirch</code></li>
              <li><code>--englishoak</code></li>
              <li><code>--fieldmaple</code></li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="list f7">
