              <li><code>--holly</code></li>
              <li><code>--horsechestnut</code></li>
              <li><code>--rowan-berries</code></li>
              <li><code>--rowan-leaves</code></li>
              <li><code>--silverbirch</code></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Horisontal Rules</h3>
          <div class="bt">
            <p class="f6">
              Currently if you include a horisontal rule in the markup from a
              flourish component, it will be rendered, using the <code
                >.dropcap .dk-color-name</code
              > as an accent color. This only works when the the horisontal rule
              is passed into the Flourish component.
            </p>
